<section id="fs-idm12576960" class="multiple-choice">
<title>Review Questions</title><exercise id="fs-idm17333744">
<problem id="fs-idm69792768"><para id="fs-idm135949216">The inspiratory reserve volume measures the ________.</para>
<list id="fs-idp13787120" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha">
<item>amount of air remaining in the lung after a maximal exhalation</item>
<item>amount of air that the lung holds</item>
<item>amount of air the can be further exhaled after a normal breath</item>
<item>amount of air that can be further inhaled after a normal breath</item>
</list>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idp14088704">
<label/>
<para id="fs-idm165935552">D</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idp94151328">
<problem id="fs-idm98636592"><para id="fs-idp155001696">Of the following, which does not explain why the partial pressure of oxygen is lower in the lung than in the external air?</para>
<list id="fs-idm102149952" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha">
